# Site Philosophy Audit: "AI runs by default. Humans supervise."

Full audit of every section, headline, CTA, and meta tag on the Enorve marketing site against the core philosophy:

> **"AI handles support by default. Humans supervise, not operate."**
> Not "AI-powered support" — that's Intercom. But "support that runs itself, with humans in control."

---

## ✅ Sections Already Aligned

These sections correctly express the philosophy — AI-first with human oversight:

| Section | Why It Works |
|---|---|
| **Hero** (updated) | "Your AI handles support. Your team handles exceptions." |
| [GovernedAutonomySection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/GovernedAutonomySection.tsx) | "Governed autonomy for customer operations" — perfect framing of AI with guardrails |
| [AIEngineSection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/AIEngineSection.tsx) | "A complete support platform with deterministic AI at its core" — emphasizes governance |
| [PlatformSection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/PlatformSection.tsx) | "From conversation to resolution — automatically, safely" — AI-first with safety |
| [IsometricSection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/IsometricSection.tsx) | "From Algorithm to Accountability" — deterministic control layers |
| [EnterpriseSecuritySection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/EnterpriseSecuritySection.tsx) | Security-first, enterprise-grade — aligned |
| [LanguagesSection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/LanguagesSection.tsx) | Multilingual AI resolution — neutral, fine |
| [ConnectStackSection](file:///c:/Users/Jarvis/Documents/Enorve-Market/src/components/sections/ConnectStackSection.tsx) | Integrations — channel-focused, fine |

